{"version": 2, "width": 100, "height": 30, "timestamp": 1764950600, "env": {"SHELL": "/bin/bash", "TERM": "xterm-256color"}, "title": "HELIX brief: author the governing artifacts"}
[0.0, "o", "\r\n\u001b[2m# You have a fresh repo and one sentence of intent. Step one: author the brief \u2014 the artifacts that govern every downstream decision.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.0, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m$ tree -a -L 2\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.4, "o", ".\r\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 .claude\r\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 skills\r\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 README.md\r\n"]
[1.5, "o", "\r\n\u001b[36m> Use HELIX to frame this intent: Build a CSV-to-Parquet ingest pipeline for a healthcare claims processor.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
